<DOC><DOCNO> AP890517-0195 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-17-89 2120EST</FILEID><FIRST>r a AM-HelicopterRescue     05-17 0202</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Helicopter Rescue,0208</SECOND><HEAD>Radio Helicopter Pilot Rescues Stranded Family</HEAD><HEAD>With AM-Storms Rdp</HEAD><DATELINE>CLEBURNE, Texas (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A helicopter pilot guided his aircraftwith one hand and used the other to lift two children off theirmother's car just before it was swept into a rain-swollen creek.   Helicopters being used by two radio stations spotted thestranded family, and WBAP traffic reporter Dick Siegel, guided byradio from the other craft, lowered his helicopter to the carteetering on the edge of a flooded bridge.   KPLX-KLIF helicopter pilot Ken Arnold spotted the three, and heand traffic reporter Chuck Schechner guided Siegel's rescue.   ``We hovered right behind him with our skids right over thewater,'' Schechner said. ``We were kind of keeping him straight.... We stayed behind him and talked with him.''   Siegel lifted 7-year-old Brady Laird aboard from the car's trunklid. Brady helped pull her 9-year-old sister Kelly aboard, WBAPNews Director Joe Halstead said.   ``The lady then climbed on top of the car and climbed into thecopter,'' Siegel said.   Halstead said the woman and children were stranded when shetried to drive across the flooded bridge. They climbed on top oftheir car to wait for help.</TEXT></DOC>